    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-01T00:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-01T00:35:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.24591/11–145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-01T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 1, 1945—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 3—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>900. British Embassy yesterday publicly announced that withdrawal British troops
                    from Hamadan and Khorramabad is to be completed today and Kermanshah will be
                    evacuated by Nov 21. Announcement says by beginning Dec only British troops in
                    Iran will be detachments Andimeshk. Ahwaz, Abadan and Khorramshahr and few
                    individuals at Tehran, Hamadan, Khorramabad and Kermanshah. Adds that British
                    authorities are ready to hand over security in oilfields to Iranian forces and
                    assume transfer will be complete by end Nov.<note n="40" xml:id="d398fn40">For
                        statement made by Mr. Bevin on November 21, 1945, regarding the progress of
                        withdrawing British troops from Iran, see <hi rend="italic">Parliamentary
                            Debates</hi>, House of Commons, 5th series, vol. 416, col. 546.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Dept as 900, repeated Moscow as 262 and London as 71.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
